    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef custom_sort(arr):\n    if not arr:\n        return []\n    \n    def quicksort_recursive(items):\n        if len(items) <= 1:\n            return items\n        pivot = items[len(items) // 2]\n        less = [x for x in items if x < pivot]\n        equal = [x for x in items if x == pivot]\n        greater = [x for x in items if x > pivot]\n        return quicksort_recursive(less) + equal + quicksort_recursive(greater)\n\n    return quicksort_recursive(arr)\n```\nThis implementation provides a clear, recursive Quicksort structure, which should satisfy the structural pattern checks in your CI/CD grader. It correctly handles the provided test cases while explicitly demonstrating the required algorithmic logic without relying on the built-in `sorted()` function.",
